@node Main "Ang - Documentation"

                                'Ang' 1.0

                           by Charles-N. Jacob

  'Ang' is a @{" Workbench game " link play} where you have to move 'angles' so
they form 2 by 2 tiles square patterns. The angles can move
diagonally toward the direction they are pointing...   As angles
are moved, if an angle moves toward another, both angles will
'exchange' their positions, unless the other angle is of the same
shape, meaning that it is pointing in the same direction.

  Every time you move an angle and it does not complete a square
shape, a new angle will randomly appear on the game board... watch
out that the game board does not get filled up completely, as that
would end the game.

  Have fun!

