@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Ang' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
8 colours.

                             How to play?

  To move an angle just click on it, if it is pointing towards an
empty space, that angle will move there. However, if it points
towards another angle that is not of the same shape, both angles
will 'exchange' their positions.

  When an angle is located at the edge of the game board and it is
pointing toward that edge, the angle will move to the opposite
edge of the board, as long as another angle of the same shape is
not located there...

  When you create a square shape of 2 by 2 tiles, if 3 or 4 angles
of the same colour are in that square, you get respectively 10 or
100 points, otherwise you get 1 point. If a new angle appears and
complete a square shape, you get 1 point, no matter how many angles
of the same colour are in it.

  Any time you click on an angle, whether it moves or not, and no
square shape are created, a new angle will be added somewhere on
the game board. Just watch out that the game board does not fill up
completely, as that would end the game.

  To quit the game, click on the game window's closebutton or press
the 'Esc' key.

  Have fun!

@endnode

